
[1]empoison

   EMPOIS'ON, v.t. s as z.

   1. To poison; to administer poison to; to destroy or endanger life by
   giving or causing to be taken into the stomach any noxious drug or
   preparation. [In this sense, poison is generally used; but empoison may
   be used, especially in poetry.]

   2. To taint with poison or venom; to render noxious or deleterious by
   an admixture of poisonous substance. [This may be used, especially in
   poetry.]
